# Cursor Rules for next-service-dispatch-core

# Project Context
This guide is for church staff who will be using the guest registration system to manage visitors and approve registrations.

# General Guidelines
- Always use best practices and conventions
- Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code
- Documentation should primarily be in md files and not in the code itself. Only document in code if it would be unclear to a developer what is happening.
- Follow consistent code formatting and style
- Always build classes and methods to be unit testable. Inject in dependencies, and give reasonable defaults.

# Software and Packages to use to build this project
- Next.js version 16. Latest stable.
- Use latest stable version of TypeScript for type safety
- Use latest stable version of shadcn/ui
- Supabase will be backend
- Deployment will be Vercel
- Vitest for testing
- Playwright for E2E tests (if neccesssary)

# Code Style
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Add comments for complex logic
- Prefer composition over inheritance

